Package wellen

Class DSPModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • wellen.DSPModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DSPNodeOutputSignal, Loopable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DSPTrack
    public abstract class DSPModule
extends java.lang.Object
implements DSPNodeOutputSignal, Loopable
    a module allows to compose complex DSP modules. it is a container that may be managed by a DSPTrack.

    a module must implement the method 

    void output(Signal)
    which supplies an audio signal and may implement the method 
    void beat(int)
    which can be used to receive beat events.

      • set_length

        public void set_length​(int pLength)
        set length of a module loop. setting the length affects outpoint. e.g given an inpoint of 3, setting the length to 2 will set output to 4. note that outpoint is inclusive i.e a pattern from in- to outpoint of 3, 4, 5, … is generated.
        Parameters:
        pLength - set length of loop
